This article is a letter from President Barack Obama to the Speaker of the House of Representatives and the President Pro Tempore of the Senate, providing a supplemental consolidated report on military operations in accordance with the War Powers Resolution. The letter outlines the deployment of U.S. Armed Forces in support of counterterrorism objectives around the world, including Afghanistan, Iraq, Syria, Somalia, Yemen, Djibouti, Libya, Niger, Cameroon, Egypt, Jordan, and Kosovo. The letter emphasizes the success of these operations in degrading the capabilities of terrorist groups such as al-Qa'ida, the Taliban, and ISIL. The President states that additional measures will be taken if necessary to protect U.S. citizens and interests. The letter concludes by asserting the President's authority to conduct these operations under his constitutional and statutory powers as Commander in Chief and Chief Executive.